Spring JDBC:
    It eliminates lot of boiler plate of code , such as opening/closing of connection, handling of exceptions,
       it makes us the code looks smoother and readable
    For Spring JDBC we have to provide some basic details to make the connection to DB instance.
       -> Driver
       -> URL
       -> UserName
       -> password
  Spring JDBC has classes that has the ability to interact with databases and provide us the desired data result.
  One of such class is JDBCTemplate.

